<p>A road trip across India — from Mumbai to Goa, Delhi to Jaipur, or Bangalore to Ooty — is one of life's great pleasures. But unexpected fuel costs can quickly trip up your budget. This step-by-step guide shows you exactly how to calculate petrol expenses for any road trip before you leave home.</p>

<h2>Why Calculate Fuel Cost Before a Trip?</h2>
<p>Knowing your trip fuel cost allows you to set an accurate travel budget, split costs fairly among carpool partners, decide whether to drive or take a train/flight, and plan fuel stops along the route. A precise estimate prevents the common mistake of under-budgeting and running short of cash mid-trip.</p>

<h2>The Trip Fuel Cost Formula</h2>
<div style="background:#f4f6f8;padding:20px;border-left:5px solid #4f46e5;margin:20px 0;border-radius:8px;">
    <strong>Fuel Litres Needed = Trip Distance / Vehicle Mileage (km/l)</strong><br>
    <strong>Total Fuel Cost = Fuel Litres × Current Fuel Price (₹/litre)</strong><br>
    <strong>Cost Per Person = Total Fuel Cost / Number of People</strong>
</div>

<h2>Step-by-Step: Mumbai to Goa Road Trip</h2>
<p>Distance: 590 km one-way (1,180 km round trip). Car mileage: 14 km/l. Petrol price: ₹106/litre. Passengers: 4.</p>
<ol>
    <li>One-way fuel = 590 / 14 = 42.14 litres</li>
    <li>One-way cost = 42.14 × ₹106 = ₹4,467</li>
    <li>Round trip cost = ₹4,467 × 2 = <strong>₹8,934</strong></li>
    <li>Per person (4 people) = ₹8,934 / 4 = <strong>₹2,234/person</strong></li>
</ol>

